# Reason: Five months of operational evidence demonstrated
# that the auto-remediation pattern produced more risk than
# value. Specifically: 51 historical autonomous code edits
# (30 against explicit instructions forbidding framework.py
# modification), structurally broken audit trail due to a
# schema-alias misconfiguration, and demonstrated capacity
# to regress code correctness during LLM-gated iteration
# (on 2026-04-23, iterations 1-6 against agent_orchestrator.py
# culminated in iteration 5 introducing a broken reference to
# an undefined method).
#
# This file is preserved for forensic and reference purposes.
# It is NOT loaded by the agent runner — run.py's ALL_AGENTS
# list no longer imports CodeDoctorAgent (see commit 520e52e).
# The ops.agent_registry row is marked is_active=false with a
# config-field tombstone recording the retirement.
#
# Do not re-enable without deliberate architectural review.
# If the auto-remediation pattern is worth rebuilding, it
# should be rebuilt as a proposal-only agent (writes to
# ops.pending_approvals, never applies autonomously) with
# framework-level path whitelisting on write_file/patch_file.
#
# Historical evidence preserved:
#   - ops.code_fixes: 51 audit rows (table comment added)
#   - agents/*.bak: on-disk backups of files code-doctor wrote
#   - 21 CODEDOCTOR_*.md analysis files in this directory
#   - Git history: no rewrites
#
